The Khenari are jackal-headed humanoids whose civilization emerged from the mortuary-legal culture of Akh'enet. They are psychopomps, balance-keepers, and death-administrators — a people who built their entire society around managing the threshold between living and dead as a civic institution. Death is transaction, not interruption. Mourning follows record-keeping, not the reverse. Physical description: slightly shorter than average humans with lean frames built for long desert travel. Elongated tapered muzzles between jackal and wolf in profile; tall triangular ears rotating independently. Eyes amber to deep gold with slit pupils widening dramatically in low light. Fur ranges from sandy tawny through warm brown to deep charcoal. Jackal tail functions as involuntary emotional indicator. Ritual scarification along outer ears and muzzle in traditional communities encodes lineage, professional role, and number of death-ledgers formally closed. Stat profile: STR 12, INT 18, WIS 22, DEX 16, CON 16. Strong in Shadow and Holy; weak in Physical and Fire; resistant to Shadow and Mental; susceptible to Fire and Physical. Racial skills: sneak, spell critical damage, spell critical. The Doctrine of Ninth Descent governs spiritual life: lawful passage from life to death requires nine administrative stages — declaration, witness, inventory, debt resolution, lineage notation, route closure, name sealing, silence passage, verdict. Deaths that skip stages produce unlawful passage: ongoing spiritual instability affecting the dead person's family for generations. The death-ledger is a sacred object. Falsifying records is heresy. Three Akh'enet factions divide Khenari internal politics: Reed Ledger Wardens (practical, water-first), Moon Sepulchrists (ritual, underworld-administrative), Salt Jackal Reclaimers (commercial, road-debt focused).

